{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-14758/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-14758"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:47:58"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, pan"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Man exits room, two women flank his sides"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-14758","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-14758"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1/412d6ad5-5d32-4ffd-ac14-093d272bf5aa","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T19:02:14.235Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>“The choices of the elements of this Grand Salon were influenced by that of Dior in the late ‘40s and ‘50s,” according to set decorator Véronique Melery. Acknowledging Daniel Day-Lewis's heavy involvement in many aspects of the production, she continues: “Daniel chose the red of the curtains, dark red with hints of black. We incorporated silk taffetas in three different tones for the curtains/draperies and the covers of a variety of pieces of seating” (Burg, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW261969964 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.setdecorators.org/?art=film_decor_features&amp;SHOW=SetDecor_Film_Phantom_Thread\"><u>Set Decore</u></a>”). The lush color reflects the opulence of this era of fashion design, as well as, in this case, the passion that Alma brings out of Reynolds.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-14758/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:42.49204949070581,44.27465159627346,291.1474920382165,215.95342356687897"}}}]}]}]}